The State Capture Commission hears oral evidence from former Public Enterprises Minister, Malusi Gigaba. Earlier,  Transnet CFO Anoj Singh denied allegations that he leaked and e-mailed sensitive documents to consultancy firm Trillian which belonged to Gupta associate Salim Essa. Singh was questioned by the commission regarding tender irregularities of the 1 064 locomotives. The deal ballooned from R39 billion to R 54 billion. Singh has maintained that the increases were due to currency fluctuations and other unforeseen expenses. Below is Malusi Gigaba’s testimony:    